&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS SECONDMENT FOR 18 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a suitably experienced, motivated Specialist Biomedical Scientist with the requisite knowledge and skills in Laboratory Immunology&lt;span&gt; to complete our Senior Scientist team in Ysbyty Gwynedd, Bangor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will have a focus on quality and service delivery and the interpersonal skills to take the team with you as you deliver change and improvement working with our established Blood Sciences site management team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are an experienced, MSC level qualified Scientist looking for the ideal opportunity to take the next step on your career in a team that will offer challenge and opportunity whilst providing professional &amp; personal support; or if you are an experienced Senior BMS looking for new opportunity and challenges then come and see what BCUHB and North Wales has to offer - you won’t be disappointed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Helen Crabbe or Elin Davies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Immunology Laboratory Manager/ Biomedical Scientist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01248 384654 &lt;/p&gt;
